According to the [[2020 United States census|2020 U.S. census]], Mohawk had a population of 388.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2020 Race and Population Totals |url=https://data.census.gov/table?g=160XX00US2654820&tid=DECENNIALPL2020.P1 |access-date=2023-08-01 |website=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> In 2020, more than 90% of its population was [[Non-Hispanic whites|non-Hispanic white]].

Culturally, the majority of its population has [[English Americans|English]] ancestry (17.2%), though [[German Americans|German]] (13.9%) and [[Irish Americans|Irish]] (11%) were the second and third-largest ancestries.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2021 Ancestry Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/table?g=160XX00US2654820&tid=ACSDP5Y2021.DP02 |access-date=2023-08-01 |website=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> Through the 2021 American Community Survey, the median age of its population was 38.4.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2021 Age and Sex Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/table?g=160XX00US2654820&tid=ACSST5Y2021.S0101 |access-date=2023-08-01 |website=United States Census Bureau}}</ref>

As of 2021's census estimates, the community had a median household income of $47,188 and 23.8% of the population lived at or below the poverty line.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mohawk CDP, Michigan |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Mohawk_CDP,_Michigan?g=160XX00US2654820 |access-date=2023-08-01 |website=United States Census Bureau}}</ref>

